19:47.854 --> 19:48.889
Dad!

19:53.151 --> 19:54.607
Dad, help!

19:55.445 --> 19:56.776
(CREAKING)

19:58.239 --> 20:01.026
Claire, don't let go!

20:01.409 --> 20:02.910
Dad!

20:14.798 --> 20:15.753
(GRUNTS)

20:15.840 --> 20:16.829
(SIGHS IN RELIEF)

20:19.677 --> 20:21.759
You okay?
Peachy.

20:27.852 --> 20:30.059
Thank God.
You okay?

20:32.399 --> 20:34.230
The target's gone.

20:34.317 --> 20:36.103
He can't be far.

20:40.365 --> 20:43.573
Claire, where did
Mr. Canfield go?

20:43.660 --> 20:45.241
Leave him alone.
He doesn't want
to hurt anyone.

20:45.328 --> 20:47.694
This isn't a game,
he's very dangerous.

20:47.789 --> 20:49.325
Who are you to talk?

20:50.166 --> 20:51.906
Bringing him here?

20:52.001 --> 20:54.253
Tell me you're not
working with him
after what he did to me.

20:54.337 --> 20:56.453
Claire, you hate me,
I understand.

20:56.548 --> 20:58.584
When I touched your hand,
I could feel the pain
that I caused you,

20:58.675 --> 20:59.664
and I never meant...

20:59.759 --> 21:02.000
Shut your mouth, now.

21:02.971 --> 21:06.054
You don't get to
talk to her, ever.

21:07.016 --> 21:08.051
Look.

21:08.768 --> 21:10.224
We'll talk more about this
when we get home,

21:10.311 --> 21:13.474
but right now,
you have to tell me
where Mr. Canfield went.

21:13.565 --> 21:17.934
He's not a killer.
He's having problems
like I had problems.

21:19.446 --> 21:22.654
He just...
He didn't have
you to help him.

21:24.367 --> 21:29.031
All right. Okay,
then just let me
talk to him.

21:29.122 --> 21:32.455
If what you say is true,
we'll make other
arrangements.

21:32.542 --> 21:34.078
You can trust me,
Claire.

21:34.836 --> 21:38.203
I wouldn't send anybody
to Level 5 that
doesn't belong there.

21:43.052 --> 21:45.008
He's at the Griffith Park
carousel.

21:48.057 --> 21:49.342
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

21:55.440 --> 21:57.977
This is your plan?
Go to a bar?

21:58.067 --> 22:01.559
I haven't had a drink
in months, and they
make a mean Appletini.

22:01.654 --> 22:04.316
l'm warning you,
Adam Monroe, l'll pop you
right back into your coffin.

22:04.407 --> 22:08.025
Relax. You said
the Speedster girl
was hired, right?

22:08.119 --> 22:11.202
Well, this bar is
the go-to destination
of specials-for-hire.

22:11.289 --> 22:13.280
Specials-for-hire?
That's right.

22:13.625 --> 22:17.243
Oh, like the Cantina.
I never knew
there was such a place.

22:18.213 --> 22:20.329
Can we find out
who hired the Speedster?

22:20.423 --> 22:23.460
Hello,
that's why we're here.

22:23.551 --> 22:28.887
Just leave everything to me.
And try and look tough.

22:33.144 --> 22:37.604
(BOTH SPEAKING JAPANESE)

22:41.736 --> 22:45.945
Barkeep. The usual,
and make it snappy.

22:51.496 --> 22:53.452
Hello, Milosh.

22:53.540 --> 22:56.282
How dare you
come in here?

22:56.376 --> 23:01.712
Look, I didn't know she was
your wife, and for the record,
she never mentioned it.

23:03.341 --> 23:04.956
(EXCLAIMING)

23:05.969 --> 23:07.459
(PEOPLE EXCLAIMING)

23:09.556 --> 23:11.262
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

23:24.237 --> 23:25.226
(SIGHS)

23:25.446 --> 23:26.435
(DOOR OPENING)

23:26.531 --> 23:27.691
NATHAN: What happened
to Peter?

23:27.782 --> 23:29.943
I put him in
a medically-induced coma.

23:30.034 --> 23:32.901
What?
Your brother
tried to kill me.

23:32.996 --> 23:34.076
VVhy?

23:34.163 --> 23:37.405
He took Sylar's ability,
and now he's suffering
the consequences.

23:37.500 --> 23:39.661
We're in a lot
of trouble, Nathan.

23:42.255 --> 23:45.918
Mom, that's Tracy Strauss.
Tracy, my mom.

23:46.009 --> 23:48.716
I know who she is,
and why she's come.

23:48.803 --> 23:50.134
I heard you saw
Dr. Zimmerman.

23:50.221 --> 23:51.757
How do you know
Dr. Zimmerman?

23:51.848 --> 23:55.386
He worked for the Company
many years ago
in research and development.

23:55.476 --> 23:56.727
Very bright.

23:56.811 --> 24:00.303
Then you understand
what he did to me?
You can help me.

24:00.398 --> 24:03.765
No, I'm afraid
that's not possible.
His work was classified.

24:03.860 --> 24:05.942
You want me to go
public with this?

24:07.655 --> 24:09.395
What are you hiding,
Mom?

24:14.537 --> 24:16.528
Zimmerman was instrumental

24:16.623 --> 24:20.115
in the Company's
development of
synthetic abilities.

24:20.209 --> 24:21.460
Synthetic?

24:21.544 --> 24:24.502
We used the technology
on a number of infants.

24:24.589 --> 24:28.298
You were one of them, Tracy.
As were your sisters,
Niki and Barbara.

24:33.640 --> 24:37.383
And you, Nathan,
we gave you
your ability, too.

25:03.127 --> 25:04.116
(GASPS)

25:06.631 --> 25:07.837
My God.

25:18.017 --> 25:19.473
What have you done?

25:22.480 --> 25:23.560
(GASPING)

25:23.648 --> 25:25.889
My God.

25:34.158 --> 25:35.614
I got to get you out.

25:40.456 --> 25:41.445
(DOOR CLOSING)

25:46.254 --> 25:47.664
(CLATTERING)

26:29.630 --> 26:30.619
(GROANING)

26:35.011 --> 26:36.342
Maya.

26:43.144 --> 26:44.680
I know you're in here.

26:46.230 --> 26:47.891
(CLATTERING)

26:57.825 --> 26:59.781
You have to
control your power.

27:01.662 --> 27:03.869
You don't want to be
a killer again, do you?

27:08.544 --> 27:10.125
(EXHALES)

27:13.966 --> 27:15.547
What have you done?

27:18.513 --> 27:21.505
You're a monster.

27:22.642 --> 27:24.598
I wish you hadn't said that.

27:26.521 --> 27:27.510
(MAYA GASPS)

27:34.237 --> 27:36.068
(HIRO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

27:38.074 --> 27:40.360
(AN DO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

27:49.585 --> 27:50.574
(CHUCKLES)

27:54.590 --> 27:55.579
(GROANS)

28:13.860 --> 28:15.100
It's done.

28:15.987 --> 28:18.148
What do you want me
to do about the two
Japanese guys?

28:19.282 --> 28:24.151
It's all here.
The testing,
the experimentation.

28:24.245 --> 28:25.701
Everything they did to us.

28:28.541 --> 28:30.031
It wasn't God.

28:30.126 --> 28:32.287
We were trying to
be better than God.

28:33.796 --> 28:35.002
How?

28:36.382 --> 28:39.374
By using people
as lab rats?

28:41.596 --> 28:43.132
Your own son?

28:44.640 --> 28:47.723
Your father was disappointed
that you weren't born
with the genetic code,

28:47.810 --> 28:50.222
but we thought,
because of your lineage,
your system could handle it.

28:50.313 --> 28:52.429
And obviously
we were right.

28:53.357 --> 28:54.938
Then what about me?

28:57.028 --> 28:58.609
My parents were dead.

28:59.697 --> 29:01.858
I had no one
to protect me.

29:01.949 --> 29:05.362
Tracy, what this Company
did to you in the name
of science was wrong.

29:05.453 --> 29:06.818
We know that now.

29:06.913 --> 29:09.370
And that is why
we divided
the formula and hid it,

29:09.457 --> 29:11.698
so this would never
happen again.

29:12.627 --> 29:15.494
An innocent man
is dead because of
what you did to me.

29:16.297 --> 29:19.039
Then help me,
because someone has
stolen the formula.

29:19.133 --> 29:21.875
They want to restart
this project.

29:21.969 --> 29:24.927
They want to create
a world filled
with dangerous people.

29:25.014 --> 29:29.053
Deadly, out of control.
They will destroy everything.

29:30.603 --> 29:32.218
Please help me
stop them.

29:32.313 --> 29:33.302
Go to hell.

29:35.232 --> 29:39.771
Nathan, it's why Peter took
Sylar's ability. It's why
he sacrificed himself.

29:39.862 --> 29:43.104
He knows what's gonna
happen to this world.
You do not understand.

29:43.199 --> 29:46.737
I understand, Ma.
I understand.

29:46.827 --> 29:49.364
You locked Peter up,
put a shunt in his head.

29:50.665 --> 29:57.377
You did experiments
on me and God knows
who else. Peter? Claire?

29:58.172 --> 30:01.209
Who else did you
use as your own
personal guinea pig?

30:02.343 --> 30:05.676
Nathan, listen to me.
Nathan.

30:11.560 --> 30:13.892
I'm sorry.
What's next?

30:13.980 --> 30:15.220
I know a scientist.

30:15.314 --> 30:18.181
He understands all of this
genetic stuff. If anybody
can help you, he can.

30:18.275 --> 30:19.355
Can he be trusted?

30:19.443 --> 30:21.434
Suresh? Yeah,
he's harmless.

30:36.627 --> 30:39.004
Stephen,
it's Claire.

30:40.423 --> 30:42.254
I talked to my dad.

30:48.597 --> 30:50.588
He said he's willing
to listen.

30:51.934 --> 30:53.765
It doesn't matter anymore.

30:54.645 --> 30:55.930
What happened?

30:58.983 --> 31:00.439
They never showed up.

31:02.903 --> 31:04.939
You were right, Claire.

31:05.031 --> 31:10.367
My wife, my kids,
they're afraid of me.

31:21.922 --> 31:23.708
Maybe I am a monster.

31:24.884 --> 31:26.215
Couldn't put it better.

31:26.302 --> 31:27.291
Dad, what are you doing?

31:27.386 --> 31:29.502
It's all right.
We're just talking.

31:29.597 --> 31:31.553
I'll make you a deal,
Stephen.

31:31.640 --> 31:34.177
My partner is standing
right over there by my car.

31:34.268 --> 31:38.056
You make him disappear,
and this is all over.

31:39.398 --> 31:41.980
I don't understand,
you want me to
kill your partner?

31:45.321 --> 31:46.436
(lNAUDlBLE)

31:46.781 --> 31:50.194
Do it, and I'll let you go.
I give you my word.

31:50.284 --> 31:52.946
What are you saying?
You do not have to do this.

31:53.037 --> 31:54.368
Stay out of this, Claire.

31:54.455 --> 31:56.741
She's right, I can't.
I'm not a killer.

31:56.832 --> 32:01.201
Maybe not, but he is,
and he needs
to be destroyed.

32:01.295 --> 32:03.832
Unfortunately,
I can't do it.

32:03.923 --> 32:05.504
Please...
I'm not asking.

32:07.426 --> 32:08.666
Dad,no.

32:10.054 --> 32:13.546
I'm doing this for us, Claire.
For what Sylar did to you.

32:17.311 --> 32:22.556
You people,
you've taken
everything from me.

32:24.110 --> 32:26.772
Do it. Kill him, now.

32:34.453 --> 32:36.193
What are you doing?

32:37.206 --> 32:38.867
I won't be a monster.

32:40.042 --> 32:41.202
No.

32:51.887 --> 32:54.048
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

32:54.682 --> 32:55.671
(EXHALES)

32:55.766 --> 32:58.553
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

33:23.502 --> 33:25.117
Hello, boys.

33:25.963 --> 33:26.998
Nemesis.

33:28.591 --> 33:31.799
So, my friend here
tells me that
you're looking for work.

33:31.886 --> 33:36.505
And I said,
"That's not possible.
Those goody two-shoes?"

33:40.769 --> 33:45.183
We heard about
what you are doing.
Sign us up.

33:45.274 --> 33:46.354
I'm not convinced.

33:46.442 --> 33:48.558
We have changed.
We are badasses now.

33:48.652 --> 33:50.768
Yes, we are very badass.

33:52.198 --> 33:54.530
When do we start?
Not so fast.

33:54.617 --> 33:56.448
You have to prove
yourself worthy.

33:57.953 --> 33:58.942
How do we do that?

33:59.038 --> 34:01.199
You're the one
with the powers?
Yes.

34:01.290 --> 34:02.951
I control time and space.

34:04.668 --> 34:05.874
Cool.

34:14.136 --> 34:15.467
Kill the other one.

34:15.554 --> 34:17.636
KiII Ando?
KiII Ando?

34:17.723 --> 34:21.090
Yeah, he has no powers.
What good is he to us?

34:22.645 --> 34:25.261
You kill him,
you are badass.

34:32.446 --> 34:33.947
I'm sorry,
my friend.

34:35.199 --> 34:39.533
I must make
some sacrifices
to save the world.

34:41.455 --> 34:42.410
(GROANING)

34:42.498 --> 34:43.487
(DAPHNE GASPING)

34:50.089 --> 34:51.329
Hiro.

35:12.069 --> 35:14.230
We'll talk more when
I come home, okay?

35:16.365 --> 35:17.730
Claire, wait.

35:18.742 --> 35:23.611
I know you're disappointed,
but I did what I had to do.

35:23.706 --> 35:24.946
For us.

35:26.667 --> 35:28.874
She doesn't believe
a word you're saying.

35:30.796 --> 35:32.206
She knows exactly
what you did back there.

35:32.298 --> 35:34.960
Why you didn't
take down Stephen Canfield
when you had the chance.

35:35.050 --> 35:36.301
Nobody's talking to you.

35:36.385 --> 35:40.549
Claire finally sees you
for what you are. A user.

35:40.639 --> 35:42.630
Isn't that right, Claire?

35:42.725 --> 35:44.465
You used her to try
to find that poor man,

35:44.560 --> 35:50.556
then you used him to try
to kill me, because to you
I'm nothing but a monster.

35:51.900 --> 35:54.277
He doesn't see
our humanity, Claire.

35:55.738 --> 35:57.069
He never will.

35:58.741 --> 36:02.233
Wait. You're not gonna
listen to him, are you?

36:02.328 --> 36:04.910
The man is
a deranged sociopath.
He's a killer.

36:04.997 --> 36:06.828
He's a monster.

36:06.915 --> 36:08.325
Yes.

36:08.417 --> 36:10.658
And you're my daughter.

36:10.753 --> 36:15.338
And everything I do
is to protect you.

36:15.424 --> 36:20.669
To protect this family.
Tell me you understand that.

36:24.933 --> 36:26.434
I understand.

36:30.606 --> 36:32.016
(SIGHING)

36:34.360 --> 36:36.271
It's all gonna be okay.

36:38.113 --> 36:39.649
I promise.

36:41.033 --> 36:42.523
Mom.

36:43.285 --> 36:44.400
SANDRA: Claire.

36:44.495 --> 36:48.113
Thank God,
l was so worried.

36:48.207 --> 36:51.040
Are you okay?
Because if you are,
you're so grounded.

36:51.210 --> 36:52.825
(SIGHING)
I'm sorry.

36:52.920 --> 36:55.127
I'm just glad
Meredith found you.

36:57.549 --> 36:58.755
Meredith?

37:00.302 --> 37:04.545
ERIC: Enjoying your dinner,
my dear? Eat.

37:15.651 --> 37:16.640
(SIGHS)

37:21.323 --> 37:25.566
Now, give me
a sweet kiss.

37:25.661 --> 37:27.822
Go to hell,
you filthy...

37:37.548 --> 37:38.537
(MOANS)

38:05.409 --> 38:07.024
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

38:24.219 --> 38:25.595
Oh, my God.

38:28.765 --> 38:30.426
(GASPS)

38:40.235 --> 38:43.318
Peter, tell me
you didn't
do this, please.

38:46.074 --> 38:47.610
(GASPS)

38:49.995 --> 38:51.326
(GASPING)

38:51.413 --> 38:52.402
MAN: Hello, Angela.

38:52.498 --> 38:55.114
No, it can't be.

38:56.460 --> 39:01.170
You can see the future.
I can't have that.
That's too dangerous.

39:01.256 --> 39:05.090
No, you won't succeed.
I'll stop you.

39:05.177 --> 39:06.883
Don't be ridiculous.

39:08.013 --> 39:10.004
You won't even
be able to move.

39:19.441 --> 39:21.898
ARTHUR:
You won’t even
be able to move.

39:34.957 --> 39:36.663
LINDERMAN: You're late.

39:36.750 --> 39:39.287
Have you completed
yourtask?

39:39.378 --> 39:40.584
They're on board.

39:41.046 --> 39:42.707
Even the Japanese guy.

39:44.216 --> 39:46.548
I'm not happy
about what happened.

39:46.635 --> 39:49.126
That's not what
I signed up for.
I'm not a killer.

39:50.264 --> 39:53.552
Well, it's all part
of making the world
a better place, Daphne.

39:53.642 --> 39:55.849
No pain, no gain.

39:56.979 --> 40:00.392
There's another one
you're going
to have to recruit.

40:00.482 --> 40:03.815
I'm afraid he's going
to be the most difficult.

40:09.950 --> 40:13.283
Matt Parkman?
What's his thing?

40:13.370 --> 40:17.113
He has the ability
to alter your mind.

40:17.207 --> 40:22.622
Put thoughts into your head.
Make you see things
that aren't there.

40:23.589 --> 40:25.420
Speaking of which,

40:25.507 --> 40:28.340
I finally figured out
what's been bugging me
aboutyou.

40:30.262 --> 40:35.507
I'm fast. Real fast.
I can sneak up
on everybody.

40:37.436 --> 40:39.347
Butlcant
sneak up on you.

40:46.403 --> 40:47.518
(GASPS)

40:47.613 --> 40:50.980
I knew it.
You're not really there.

40:51.825 --> 40:56.535
It's not your concern, Daphne.
Just bring me Parkman.

41:00.876 --> 41:03.083
I guess I don't really
have a choice, do I?

41:25.567 --> 41:28.058
(ARTIFICIAL RESPIRATOR
PUMPING)

41:39.164 --> 41:40.995
The team is coming
together nicely.

41:43.418 --> 41:45.875
Everything went fine,
perfect with Nathan.

41:47.381 --> 41:49.121
I messed with his head,

41:49.216 --> 41:51.673
gave him
visions of Linderman,
just like you asked.

41:51.760 --> 41:53.842
Now he thinks
he's doing God's work.

41:56.598 --> 41:57.929
Yes.

41:59.059 --> 42:00.424
Very real.

42:02.604 --> 42:07.189
Daphne is spreading the word.
We're building an army
just like you...

42:10.570 --> 42:14.563
Sorry. Knox called
just a few minutes ago.

42:16.451 --> 42:18.612
He'll have Adam Monroe
here by tomorrow.

42:20.455 --> 42:21.615
Right.

42:22.916 --> 42:24.281
Absolutely.

42:25.752 --> 42:28.038
Whatever you say goes,
Mr. Petrelli.
